&amp;#x200B;

The train was packed. He was "greeting" everyone at the doors and i was standing in front of the seats somewhere in the middle with a headache and a very shitty day behind me. I could see him, yelling with his eyes closed. I endured 1 whole song. I thought He'd stop but he kept going with a Creedence song. I was not in the mood for a bad Creedence cover.

&amp;#x200B;

